annotation.TEXT: Goal tape average so far: 213 / 7 = 30.429 stars each.

Uh, what is this? All of a sudden, the custom music stopped, and I'm just handed the secret exit on a platter here. (Also, my drink came with ice in it, and I usually prefer no ice in my drinks, but I forgot to say "no ice" while ordering this time...)
Actually, I'm now thinking that there probably wouldn't be a secret exit there, since this is only a 2-world demo, and the secret exit there normally leads to the Star World.

Okay, things are getting significantly different now. Those three green pipes I passed a few seconds ago were new (also, there was no midpoint). And now, it seems the clouds and coins that are normally high in the sky have been brought down here.
Oh, the screen stopped scrolling, so I bet this pipe leads to the ghost house.

...Huh? The secret exit opens a path to the right? Yeah, that actually makes sense to me here, because for whatever reason, as far as the programming goes for the original SMW, the path leading to the Top Secret Area is actually the normal exit, and the path to DP3 is the secret exit. I wonder why Nintendo coded it that way...
BGM: Crash Bandicoot - Temple Ruins
Aw, there's a passage to the right that I want to check out, but I don't have enough time...
I'll push it while over here this time just to make sure I'm not going to miss anything on the right side of this area.
BGM: CUSTOM - Panic!
Okay, so that leads to this pipe, which'll probably take me to where Donut Secret 2 would normally be. However, the turn now passes to BJ1, and he's going to check out Telesa Mansion #1.
And finally, regarding the vote at the very top of the list... Well... Just let me finish typing this sentence here...
Alright, there's door number 1. Guess I'll check it out...
I had to bounce off a Chuck to reach that ! coin, but that's fine. Oh, and this level actually has five ! coins in it, which seems to be rare for this hack!

So, the Green Switch Palace it is! Let's head there now with BJ1! ...Umm... This is BJ1, right? Well, his name on the status bar while I'm in a level will be in red text if he is. If it's green, then it's BJ2 instead, and I'll have screwed up the voting numbers...
Uhh... This isn't exactly a ghost house. It looks more like a castle to me. Also, I didn't even emerge from a pipe coming into this area.
Looks like we're back to mostly mushrooms again. Well, I can always replay that underwater level if I want more flowers.
By the way, what's with these defunct Bowser statues? Were they intentionally placed in an X position where they won't fire? Or did BBKaizo simply screw up?

...Uh, huh. Alright, door number 2 was obviously a failure. Let me work my way back to the !-switch again.
Heck, yeah! Killing stuff with my nose because my butt's on the ground!
Alright, here I am in the middle of Marble Zone Act 2, near the place where I can do that 17-combo. But, first, I want these rings in this little room right here...

Uhh... That's the goal. So, where's the ghost house? Also, where's the secret exit for that matter? I didn't see any key or keyhole or anything hinting at a secret exit...

Also, once again off camera, I scoured Telesa Mansion #1, but couldn't find any other exits. So, BJ1 opened up Platform Mania! up above there, while the level down here that BJ2 unlocked is The Iceberg. Also, the Bowser's Valley music sounds a bit odd...

Okay, new area, and that's a weird floating door there (I assume it's a door). I'll call it door number Hydrogen for now (yeah, I'm doing this door "numbering" thing again).
...Um, what? This doesn't look like a ghost house level to me... Well, just like with Chuck's Cave, I'm guessing I'll find a pipe or door leading to the ghost house part in a moment.
Well, there's a Telesa Block, and unfortunately, the screen won't scroll any further to the right from there, so I don't see any way to open that ? block.
